   The Economic impact of the Ebola crisis includes loss of gross domestic output , threat to food security , fall in employment and livelihoods , and decline in foreign investment .Growth has slowed in Serial Leone and is likely to fall even further. Household income has fallen , financial reserves are being used and up and large numbers of people are now food insecure.
  In Social impact and implications  progress in human development is likely to reversed due to the impact of Ebola crisis on health , education and standard of living. Almost 2 million  children have not been attending school. The diversion of development  spending , especially for roads , energy , building schools  and hospitals , to the Ebola response , could have negative impact on peace dividends.
